I investigated the difference. The fact table is already aggregated, so one row does not necessarily represent one transaction. There are 548 rows where MEASURE_VOLUME is greater than 1 (with a maximum value of 111), meaning a single row can represent multiple transactions. Therefore, COUNT(*) counts aggregated rows, while SUM(MEASURE_VOLUME) returns the actual transaction volume. For Tableau reporting, SUM(MEASURE_VOLUME) should be used when displaying transaction counts.